<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/FAO-breaks-new-ground-in-geographic-data-management" title="FAO breaks new ground in geographic data management" alt="link">FAO breaks new ground in geographic data management</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>FAO, 21 July 2004.</i> Advances in remote sensing and geographic information system (GIS) technology have led to a dramatic expansion in the geographic information available, yet access to this information remains limited. To help put this information in the hands of those who need it, FAO has developed GeoNetwork, a spatial information management system that provides access via the Internet to a wide range of geographically referenced data from a variety of sources, to support decision-makers in agriculture, forestry, fisheries and food security and to promote multidisciplinary approaches to sustainable development.</p>
							<p><span class="date">23/12/2004</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
