<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Living-modified-organisms-new-guidelines-for-risk-assessment" title="Living modified organisms: new guidelines for risk assessment" alt="link">Living modified organisms: new guidelines for risk assessment</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>FAO press release, 1 June 2004</i>: New guidelines for determining if a living modified organism (LMO) poses a hazard to plants have been published by FAO. Some 130 countries adopted this unique international standard on how to assess the risks of LMOs, including insects, fungi and bacteria, that may be harmful to plants. Report (pdf): <a href="http://www.ippc.int/servlet/BinaryDownloaderServlet/ISPM_11_2004_En.pdf?filename=1086078360577_ISPM_11_2004.pdf" target="_blank">International Standards for Phytosanitary Measures</a>  See also: <a href="http://www.ippc.int/IPP/En/default.htm" target="_blank">International Phytosanitary Portal (IPP) </a>.</p>
